headline: WM price target raised to $265 from $260 at Scotiabank
summary: Scotiabank raised the firm’s price target on WM (WM) to $265 from $260 and keeps an Outperform rating on the shares. The firm remains positive on the stock, coming away from the company’s investor day more positive on the Healthcare segment, the analyst tells investors. Scotiabank expects WM to continue raising the dividend at a “strong pace” and resume buybacks when the leverage ratio normalizes.
